Privacy Policy for Smile
Update Effective as of: March 16, 2022
Smile has published this Privacy Policy (or privacy notice) to tell you about how we collect, use, disclose and store personal information. We think transparency is important, but providing that transparency requires us to make this notice longer than we would like. That is why we have set out the highlights at the top. We have made the full notice as user-friendly as we could, but we would also welcome your questions and comments (see
Contact Us
).
Highlights of this Notice
Customers of Our Merchants
– We may obtain your personal information when we provide services to merchants, including merchants that use our services to operate loyalty programs. We process this personal information on our merchants’ behalf and recommend you review your merchant’s privacy policy and contact them with any complaints, questions or requests. We also obtain and control personal information about customers when they use our services directly, such as when they create or use the Smile wallet.
Merchants and Their Users
– Most information we collected about merchants is business information, not personal information. We use any personal information collected to support and better understand our merchants and provide and improve our services.
Website / Support Service Users
– We collect personal information you provide directly, such as your contact information, and information collected through cookies and similar tools. We use this to provide the website, support and better understand our users and provide and improve our services.
Employees / Contractors / Applicants
– If you apply for a job with Smile, we use your personal information to consider hiring you. If we hire you, we will use your personal information in connection with your employment. A separate privacy notice may apply to employees.
Application of This Notice
What this notice covers
This notice applies to all personal information that we collect, use, disclose and store when you apply for a job with Smile or access our services. Our services include the Smile wallet, which allows you to view your reward points across multiple merchants. When you create a Smile wallet, the information you provide to Smile will be subject to this notice, including any reward points information that Smile obtains from merchants in connection with your wallet. “Smile” includes Smile Inc. and any related companies anywhere in the world.
What this notice does not cover
Merchants
: As mentioned above, we process personal information for others, including merchants. Please direct any complaints, questions or requests related to your personal information directly to those merchants. In the event you are not satisfied with how they respond, you may contact us directly, but we cannot guarantee we will be able to address it. If you do not create a Smile wallet, Smile does not control your reward point information. If you create a Smile wallet, each of Smile and the applicable merchant will control a copy of your reward points and each will know if your reward point totals change, such as when you earn new points or spend points.
Non-Personal Information
: Information about your business, including your business contact information, is not typically personal information. Anonymized information is also not considered personal information for the purposes of this notice. We may anonymize any personal information in our custody, in which case it will cease to be personal information.
In some situations, we may rely on exemptions or other permitted conduct under applicable laws, including to collect, use, disclose or store personal information for purposes not described in this notice. We provide services to merchants in many jurisdictions and privacy practices may be adopted to address the specific privacy requirements of particular jurisdictions. If you are unsure if or how this notice applies to you,
contact us
.
Changes to this Notice
Please note that we may update this notice from time to time to reflect changes in our privacy practices by providing you with notice of the changes. Notice includes but is not restricted to posting a link to the new notice, posting a new notice at smile.io/privacy-policy, or sending you a link to the new notice via contact information you have provided to us. Such changes will be effective with respect to your use of Smile’s services after Smile has given notice of the changes. Please review this notice periodically to see whether it has been updated. Any use of Smile’s services by you after we provide notice constitutes your acceptance of those changes.
Processing of Personal Information
Much of the personal information we process is necessary to provide our services and meet our contractual obligations. In most other situations, we rely on our legitimate interest (which, in some countries, would be “implied consent” or a legal exception to the consent requirement, such as where the processing is to prevent fraud). The specific purposes for which we process personal information include to:
communicate with you
track and process your purchases and report back to you as appropriate
administer, manage, test and improve our services
better understand the services, such as through reporting and analytics
deliver content and information to third parties including other merchants and their customers
market and advertise our services
fulfil any other purpose that would be reasonably apparent to the average person at the time of collection
While not stated as a purpose below, we may also use any personal information:
For security purposes, including to detect, prevent and investigate potential fraud
Where required or permitted by law
We may also request express consent to process your personal information in some circumstances, such as when you sign up as a merchant or a user for a merchant or when you visit our website and we use cookies or when you create a Smile wallet. We may also de-personalize information, such as through anonymization or aggregation. We may use and disclose such information for any purpose, as it will no longer identify you or any other person.
